# Trocado / Cordato — manual HTTP requests (REST Client / JetBrains HTTP Client)
#
# Start the app first:  uv run poe serve   (uvicorn on 127.0.0.1:8000)
# Then click "Send Request" above each block.
#
# Transitional state: only POST /budgets is wired, the store is in-memory (data is lost on restart),
# and `person_id` still comes back as the "person_id" stub until the X-Person-Id identity lands.

@host = http://127.0.0.1:8000

### Create a budget (happy path) -> 201 Created
POST {{host}}/budgets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": "500.00",
  "start_date": "2026-06-01",
  "end_date": "2026-06-30",
  "note": "mercado"
}

### Create a budget without a note (note is optional) -> 201 Created
POST {{host}}/budgets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": "1200.00",
  "start_date": "2026-07-01",
  "end_date": "2026-07-31"
}
